Subject: Layered Activation Inspection Realization

Description: SOP-HG record for the lightweight deeper inspection pattern and framework periphery naming.

@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\attention_layers\LayeredActivationInspection.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\source_documents\2026-06-24_layered_activation_inspection\Dictated_Layered_Activation_Inspection_Source.sop

& [SOPHypergraphRecord] is layered_activation_inspection_086
  + [record_type] is periphery_realization
  + [focus_subject] is layered activation inspection
  + [inside] is activation layer trace, subject inquiry queue, file surface, deeper inquiry terms, semantic pointers, correlation weights, governance review, framework periphery, declaration network window, and realization compile packet
  + [boundary] is Pinky .sop authority, source preservation, bounded depth, inspected evidence, named framework periphery, and no runtime mutation
  + [outside] is hidden native activation, exhaustive SOP network loading, proof by heat, unbounded traversal, worker mutation, and unrelated workspace changes

  = realization: deeper inspection needs a bounded layer trace so a subject can expand into the SOP declaration network without flooding focus
  = framework_periphery: each subject can name its larger framework context in periphery, then admit only a narrow declaration window when needed
  = caution: framework periphery is context, not proof that the whole framework was inspected
  = wisdom: new realizations should be compiled from inspected layers plus governance receipt, not from association heat alone

/ [SubjectInquiry] -(Feeds)> [LayeredActivationInspection], [inspection_queue]
/ [LayeredActivationInspection] -(Inspects)> [ActivationLayerStrata], [activation_layer_trace]
/ [NarrativeSubjectFileTable] -(Names)> [framework_periphery_set], [subject_key]
/ [LayeredActivationInspection] -(Bounds)> [declaration_network_window], [uninspected_network]
/ [RealizationCompilePattern] -(Emits)> [SOPHypergraphRecord], [governance_receipt]

(layered_activation_inspection_realization) :subject_key: /layer_trace and framework_periphery/ |uninspected_network|
  + [subject_key] is the subject receiving deeper inspection
  + [layer_trace] is the inspected activation strata
  + [framework_periphery] is the named larger context around the subject
  |uninspected_network| weak edges, skipped declarations, unresolved layers, and overbroad framework expansion
